The system provides an unbelievably smooth double-action-only trigger stroke. A patented offset barrel places the trigger mechanism beside the barrel lug, raising the shooter's hand close to the centerline of the bore. This, combined with the ergonomically designed grips, results in a remarkable degree of shooting comfort and control with reduced muzzle flip and felt recoil. Every Kahr pistol is made in accordance with the strictest international manufacturing standards and is individually tested before it is sold.

The PF-9 retains the best features from our P-11 and P-3AT pistols combined into the flattest and lightest single stack 9mm configuration ever made. The barrel, locking system, slide stop, assembly pin, front sight, recoil springs and guide rod are adapted from the P-11. All prices are assuming I have to drive approximately 1 hour to meet. The closer we meet, the lower my prices. No shipping.
1)      Ruger 10/22 (22 LR) Carbine- Wood stock and blued barrel. I purchased this firearm new in 2013, and have put approximately 1000 rounds through it. Comes with factory box, lock, 10 rd mag, a BX25 mag, and 525 rds of Federal bulk HP ammo. $300
2)      CZ-82 (9x18)- Stock pistol with 2 factory mags. I love shooting and carrying this gun, but as I said, some things have to go. Includes a High Noon Split Decision holster, 100 rds of 9x18 FMJ rounds and 25 Hornady Critical Defense rounds. $400
3)      Bulgarian Makarov (9x18)- bought in non-working condition, replaced a trigger bar, and it works perfectly. Finish is in great shape, and internals look good. Comes with 4 factory mags, Barsony Leather pancake holster and double mag pouch, a set of Makawrap grips, 100 rds of FMJ ammo, and 25 rds of Hornday Custom defense ammo. $500  
4)      Beretta 85F (380 ACP)- satin nickel finish and wood grips from the factory. Great little shooter, and even prettier to look at. Gun comes with 1 beat up mag that works about 3/4 of the time, and 3 factory mags that are 100% flawless, as well as the factory box. I have a small bag of factory ammo, approx. 20 rds. $600
5)      Hi Point 995 (9mm)- old style carbine with a camo painted stock. This is my bedside long gun, and it has been a blast. The paint job actually looks really good, and I don’t even like camo. Includes 2 mags, and an ATI stock that is fully functional, but is missing a cover plate and some screws. I used it without both and the gun shoots like a dream. Comes with 100rds of WWB ammo and 50 rds of 147 gr HP ammo. $325
6)      CZ P07 Duty (9mm)- this gun is fairly new to me, but spat out 200 rounds during a range day like it was going out of style. I had two malfunctions with CZ 75B mags (a ProMag and a 10 round mag), but absolutely no failures with Factory CZ P07 mags, 16 rd factory CZ 75 B mags, or 16 rounds Mec Gar CZ 75B mags. The gun has been stippled, and had the feed ramp polished. Comes with 2 mags, factory box, and 100rds of WWB ammo. $400
7)      Ruger Security Six (357 Mag)- I love this gun, but I gotta do what I gotta do. Stainless Steel gun with a 6 inch barrel, this is about as classy a revolver you can get that isn’t a Smith and Wesson, and nothing is stronger. This has been my nightstand gun, and I have no complaints about it. Lockup and timing are excellent. Gun comes with factory manga grips, factory target grips, and 50 rds of ammo. $550
8)      Beretta 950BS Minx 4” (22 Short)- this is a funky little pistol that you don’t see very often. Most people have seen the Beretta tip up pocket pistols (Bobcat, Tomcat, etc). Before those came out, you had the Minx and the Jetfire (25 ACP). The Jetfire remained, and the Minx was replaced. In addition to the pocket sized versions, there were some made with 4 inch barrels. This is one of them. It comes with the factory box, 2 magazines, and 150 rds of 22 short ammo. $450
